PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F376A1777669904
OL,3,CMayor accuses council officials of
OL,4,Champering bin strike deal
OL,6,FThe comments come after council leader
OL,7,FJohn Cotton said a deal with Unite the
OL,8,FUnion was "within sight" on Monday.
OL,10,FBut the council press office later
OL,11,Fsaid Cotton had been speaking on
OL,12,Fbehalf of the Labour Party, not the
OL,13,Fauthority itself ` pointing to a
OL,14,Fdivide between elected members and
OL,15,Fofficers.
OL,26,@pD@KOUpD@XO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G2/17
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,377,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F376A1777669904
OL,3,CMayor accuses council officials of
OL,4,Champering bin strike deal
OL,6,FCriticising officers and government-
OL,7,Fappointed commissioners, Parker said:
OL,8,F"I don't think some very important
OL,9,Fpeople at the council have put enough
OL,10,Fwork and effort into it. Almost eight
OL,11,For nine months passed without anyone
OL,12,Fengaging with Unite.
OL,14,F"You'll have to ask officers and
OL,15,Fcommissioners why they didn't put that
OL,16,Fwork and that effort in... why they
OL,17,Fdidn't take what was needed as
OL,18,Fseriously and why they were not as
OL,19,Fcommitted to it as they should have
OL,20,Fbeen."
OL,26,@pD@AOUvD@AOU|D@FO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G3/17
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,377,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F376A1777669904
OL,3,CMayor accuses council officials of
OL,4,Champering bin strike deal
OL,6,FAsked if he backed the Mayor's
OL,7,Fcomments, Cotton said: "I would like
OL,8,Fto thank the Mayor for the
OL,9,Fconstructive role that he has played
OL,10,Fin this breakthrough following months
OL,11,Fof frustration which means the end of
OL,12,Fthe dispute is within sight.
OL,14,F"I remain committed to continue
OL,15,Fworking with officers, who have been
OL,16,Fdoing complex work to navigate a
OL,17,Fchallenging situation, to deliver this
OL,18,Fdeal after the election through the
OL,19,Fformal processes."
OL,26,@oD@XOUvD@AOU{D@RO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G4/17
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
