OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F376A1777669904
OL,3,CMayor accuses council officials of
OL,4,Champering bin strike deal
OL,6,FSince the start of the year, talks
OL,7,Fhave been under way to revive a deal
OL,8,Fthat was close to agreement last
OL,9,Fsummer. Unite the Union has praised
OL,10,Fthe involvement of Lord Brendan
OL,11,FBarber, who has helped mediate
OL,12,Fdiscussions.
OL,14,FThose talks involved Unite general
OL,15,Fsecretary Sharon Graham, Cotton and
OL,16,FParker, but not council officers.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4         G14/17
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,377,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37615
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F376A1777669904
OL,3,CMayor accuses council officials of
OL,4,Champering bin strike deal
OL,6,FParker added: "I know that if the team
OL,7,Fat the council had really put the work
OL,8,Fand effort in, and approached this in
OL,9,Fthe way that myself, Brendan and John
OL,10,Fhave been since the turn of the year,
OL,11,Fthis deal could have been done a lot
OL,12,Fearlier."
OL,26,@nD@OOUtD@IO]
